</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328653BB44BFFE0A9B2D0A8FAAFA5CB" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D36B0B44BFFE0A9B2D0A8FAAFA5CB" blockId="21.[151,1436,151,500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A9B2D0A8FEC9A5EF" bold="true" box="[201,317,440,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0ABE5D0A7FCF6A5F0" box="[670,770,439,463]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Agalliini">Agalliini</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0AA73D0A8FC15A5EF" box="[776,993,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sinoagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0AA73D0A8FC15A5EF" box="[776,993,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sinoagallia serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27557D9B44BFFE0AA93D0A8FBB5A5EF" box="[1000,1089,440,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0AA93D0A8FBB5A5EF" bold="true" box="[1000,1089,440,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be recognized by the large size, reticulated venation and pitted thorax and forewings in addition to the characteristic aedeagus and style.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
